Place helper scripts, such a btest-diff canonifiers, in this directory.
Note that Zeek versions 4.1 and newer include their btest tooling as part
of the installation. Take a look at the folder reported via

  zeek-config --btest_tools_dir

for scripts, PRNG seeds, and pcaps you might be able to reuse.

MMS log contract checks:

  check-mms-log-contract exists <log>
  check-mms-log-contract fields <log> <field>...
  check-mms-log-contract enum <log> <field> <allowed-value>...
  check-mms-log-contract empty <log> <field>...

Use these from btest cases after a Zeek run generates logs. The `fields`,
`enum`, and `empty` commands read Zeek ASCII logs with `zeek-cut`; `empty`
accepts Zeek's standard unset (`-`) and empty string (`(empty)`) markers.
